# sv

> Control a running runsv service
> More information: https://manpages.ubuntu.com/manpages/latest/man8/sv.8.html

- Start a service:

`sudo sv up {any something}`

- Stop a service:

`sudo sv down {any something}`

- Get service status:

`sudo sv status {any something}`

- Reload a service:

`sudo sv reload {any something}`

- Start a service, but only if it's not running and don't restart it if it stops:

`sudo sv once {any something}`
